Use an Existing Amazon Connect Instance Integrated by Salesforce

Set up your Service Cloud Voice contact center with your existing Amazon Connect instance. Let Salesforce Help you integrate Voice with your existing Amazon Connect instance.

Before integrating, ensure that:

* You have one of the Hours of operation as Basic Hours in your Amazon Connect instance.
* You have all required resources such as S3 bucket, CTR data stream, Kinesis video stream, and Contact Lens stream in your AWS account.

From Setup, enter Partner Telephony in the Quick Find box, then select Partner Telephony Contact Centers. Click Create Contact Center.

Specify Amazon Connect as the telephony provider, use an existing instance, and enter:

* Instance ID
* ARN of the IAM role that you created earlier
* AWS permissions boundary Amazon Resource Name (ARN) if set

Click Next, optionally add users to your Amazon Connect instance, and click Done. It can take a few minutes to create the contact center.

To manage the contact center after it's created, under Setup, enter Partner Telephony Contact Centers in the Quick Find box, and select Partner Telephony Contact Centers.

If the contact center fails to be created, Salesforce sends you an email to help you resolve the issue. Now that you've created your contact center, it's time to configure it.

Configure AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) Role for Voice
title: Setting Up Service Cloud Voice with an Existing Amazon Connect Instance
